<script id="gtm-mip-engagement-timer" type="text/javascript">
// originally created by LunaMetrics - 2016
    (function(document, window, undefined) {
      
      // Cross-browser compliant event listener
function addEvent(el, evt, fn) { if (el.addEventListener) { el.addEventListener(evt, fn); } else if (el.attachEvent) { el.attachEvent('on' + evt, function(evt) { fn.call(el, evt); }); } else if (typeof el['on' + evt] === 'undefined' || el['on' + evt] === null) { el['on' + evt] = function(evt) { fn.call(el, evt); }; } } 
function removeEvent(el, evt, fn) { if (el.removeEventListener) { return el.removeEventListener(evt, fn); } if (el.detachEvent) { return el.detachEvent('on' + evt, fn); } if (el['on' + evt] === fn) { return el['on'] = null; } }; 
      
      
        var counter = 0;
        var resetTimeoutEvents = ['mousemove', 'touchstart', 'scroll', 'keydown'];
        var engagementInterval,
            engagementTimeout,
            hidden, 
            visibilityChange;
    
        // Vendor fill
        if (typeof document.hidden !== "undefined") {
    
          // Opera 12.10 and Firefox 18 and later support 
          hidden = "hidden";
          visibilityChange = "visibilitychange";
          
        } else if (typeof document.mozHidden !== "undefined") {
            
          hidden = "mozHidden";
          visibilityChange = "mozvisibilitychange";
          
        } else if (typeof document.msHidden !== "undefined") {
            
          hidden = "msHidden";
          visibilityChange = "msvisibilitychange";
          
        } else if (typeof document.webkitHidden !== "undefined") {
            
          hidden = "webkitHidden";
          visibilityChange = "webkitvisibilitychange";
          
        }
    
        setEngagementTimeout();
        registerTimeoutEvents();
        setEngagementInterval();
    
        if(visibilityChange) {         
          addEvent(document, visibilityChange, function() {
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);    
            if(!document[hidden]) {    
              setEngagementInterval();   
            }   
          });  
        } else {        
          addEvent(window, 'blur', function() {    
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);    
          });    
          addEvent(window, 'focus', function() {    
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);
            setEngagementInterval();    
          });    
        }
    
        function registerTimeoutEvents() {    
          for(i = resetTimeoutEvents.length; i > -1; i--) {    
            var _event = resetTimeoutEvents[i];
            addEvent(window, _event, resetEngagementTimeout);    
          }    
        }
    
        function setEngagementInterval() {    
          engagementInterval = setInterval(function() {    
            counter++;
            window['dataLayer'].push({
              'event': 'engagementTimer',
              'attributes': {
                'counter': counter * 15
              }
            });    
          }, Number({{MMFW - CONFIG - Engagement Timer Interval Milliseconds}}) );    
        }
    
        function setEngagementTimeout() {            
          engagementTimeout = setTimeout(function() {            
            clearInterval(engagementInterval);
            engagementInterval = false;    
          }, Number({{MMFW - CONFIG - Engagement Timer Idle Milliseconds}}) + 1 );    
        }
    
        function resetEngagementTimeout() {    
          // Clear our events
          for(i = resetTimeoutEvents.length; i > -1; i--) {    
            var _event = resetTimeoutEvents[i];
            removeEvent(window, _event, resetEngagementTimeout);    
          }    
          setTimeout(function() {    
            // Re-register our idle reset events in one seconds
            registerTimeoutEvents();    
          }, 1500);
    
          if(!engagementInterval) {
    
            setEngagementInterval();
    
          }
    
          clearTimeout(setEngagementTimeout);
          setEngagementTimeout();
    
        }

    })(document, window);
</script>
